{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780129106865,"sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_YUpYCAikOHwtH9wKuYaV7277","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 002: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\n3: description: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 002\"\n7:   - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Authored phase scaffold spec (planned)\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Execute rename after Phase 001 impact map converges\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 0\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 002 — Rename deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Implementation (rename / refactor)\n29: **Status:** Planned (depends on Phase 001 rename impact map)\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Rename the skill `deep-agent-improvement` to `deep-improvement` across every surface so the name reflects its real scope (agents + models + skills). The `-agent-` infix is now misleading.\n36: \n37: ## 2. Scope (surface list — confirmed/expanded by Phase 001 RQ6)\n38: \n39: - `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` → `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/` (dir + `SKILL.md` `name:`/frontmatter/triggers/keywords).\n40: - Commands referencing the skill path: `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` (and the new `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop`) — update skill-path references. **Command verbs are NOT renamed** unless Phase 001 shows a reason; the agent-improvement command still improves agents.\n41: - Agent file `.opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md` + runtime mirrors `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`.\n42: - Skill-advisor graph (`system-skill-advisor/.../skill-graph.json`), `descriptions.json`, advisor metadata; run advisor rebuild.\n43: - Cross-references: sentinel `sk-prompt-models`, root `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` agent-routing entries, any other skills/docs that name `deep-agent-improvement`.\n44: - Internal self-references inside the skill's own references/scripts/README.\n45: \n46: ## 3. Approach\n47: \n48: Use `git mv` for the directory to preserve history; then a tracked find-and-replace across the confirmed surface list; then advisor rebuild + validate. Agent-name decision (`@deep-agent-improvement` → `@deep-improvement`?) recorded explicitly in this phase's `decision-record.md`.\n49: \n50: ## 4. Success criteria\n51: \n52: - Zero dangling `deep-agent-improvement` references where `deep-improvement` is intended (grep-clean, allowing intentional historical mentions in archives).\n53: - Skill-advisor rebuild + `advisor_validate` green; skill resolvable under the new name.\n54: - Lane A (`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`) and Lane B (`/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`) still run.\n55: - `validate.sh --strict` green for this phase.\n56: \n57: ## 5. Out of scope\n58: \n59: Lane C build (Phase 003); doc/README three-lane rewrite beyond what the rename requires (Phase 004).\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 002: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\ndescription: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n  - \"122 phase 002\"\n  - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored phase scaffold spec (planned)\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Execute rename after Phase 001 impact map converges\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 0\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md","time":{"start":1780129106859,"end":1780129106864}},"id":"prt_e77f68763001bQHCKjsZq84PhD","sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","messageID":"msg_e77f677d1001j5rFLjhe3YY60N"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780129107959,"sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_RjfgyPgeYSMIkMCQ1chU4361","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-002.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-002.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"model\":\"deepseek\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.55,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"iter2\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-01\",\"label\":\"Three instrumentation approaches for resource-load capture: (1) CLI output parse — regex-match Read()/Glob() calls from dispatched stdout, zero changes to existing binaries; (2) tool-proxy wrapper — spawn child process with structured trace collection; (3) OpenCode MCP intercept — capture tool_use blocks at the transport layer. Approach 1 is recommended as the default, layered with Approach 3 for high-fidelity mode.\",\"iteration\":2}\n3: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-02\",\"label\":\"The expected-resource key is derived from the skills own RESOURCE_MAP + INTENT_SIGNALS + RUNTIME_ASSETS (canonical declarations from SKILL.md §2), stored in a scenario JSON file NEVER included in the prompt, and loaded only by the post-run scoring pipeline for set-membership comparison against the captured tool-call trace.\",\"iteration\":2}\n4: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-03\",\"label\":\"Contamination prevention uses a 5-category taxonomy: skill name, trigger phrases, resource paths, intent keywords, and command names — all must be absent from the prompt. A pre-dispatch grep gate (contamination-check.cjs) rejects any scenario where the prompt matches any term in the skills contamination dictionary.\",\"iteration\":2}\n5: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-04\",\"label\":\"The clean prompt construction protocol builds prompts from domain_description (the real-world problem in domain-generic terms) — never from expected_intent, expected_resources, or any skill-specific term. The APE workflow (Zhou et al. 2022, generate-instruction-from-demonstrations, score-against-held-out-truth) provides the closest prior-art analog to hint-free dispatch.\",\"iteration\":2}\n6: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-05\",\"label\":\"The end-to-end harness flow has 6 stages with one hard invariant: the expected-resource key NEVER crosses the dispatch boundary (stages 1-2 to 3). The scoring pipeline loads the key independently in stage 5, and contamination is a hard pre-dispatch gate in stage 2. Negative scenarios (irrelevance detection, adapted from BFCL v4) must be included in every batch.\",\"iteration\":2}\n7: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-06\",\"label\":\"The expected-resource key uses set membership (not ordered list) for scoring — the AI can discover resources in any order. This accommodates the iteration-001 finding that skills do not have deterministic correct chains of resource loads; the same task can be solved by reading references in different orders.\",\"iteration\":2}\n8: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-07\",\"label\":\"Toolformer (Schick et al. 2023) self-supervised API-call annotation pipeline maps to Lane C trace capture — special tokens demarcate API calls at each generation step, and the filter-by-usefulness step (L+_i vs L-_i) maps to the D4 skill-on/skill-off comparison question: did the loaded resource actually help produce better output?\",\"iteration\":2}\n9: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-08\",\"label\":\"Trace depth vs breadth: two distinct metrics emerge — initialActivationLatency (tool-calls to first skill resource, measures time-to-activation) vs fullResourceCoverage (all skill resources eventually loaded, measures depth of exploration). Both are useful and should be reported separately rather than collapsed into one metric.\",\"iteration\":2}\n\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"model\":\"deepseek\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.55,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"iter2\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-01\",\"label\":\"Three instrumentation approaches for resource-load capture: (1) CLI output parse — regex-match Read()/Glob() calls from dispatched stdout, zero changes to existing binaries; (2) tool-proxy wrapper — spawn child process with structured trace collection; (3) OpenCode MCP intercept — capture tool_use blocks at the transport layer. Approach 1 is recommended as the default, layered with Approach 3 for high-fidelity mode.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-02\",\"label\":\"The expected-resource key is derived from the skills own RESOURCE_MAP + INTENT_SIGNALS + RUNTIME_ASSETS (canonical declarations from SKILL.md §2), stored in a scenario JSON file NEVER included in the prompt, and loaded only by the post-run scoring pipeline for set-membership comparison against the captured tool-call trace.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-03\",\"label\":\"Contamination prevention uses a 5-category taxonomy: skill name, trigger phrases, resource paths, intent keywords, and command names — all must be absent from the prompt. A pre-dispatch grep gate (contamination-check.cjs) rejects any scenario where the prompt matches any term in the skills contamination dictionary.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-04\",\"label\":\"The clean prompt construction protocol builds prompts from domain_description (the real-world problem in domain-generic terms) — never from expected_intent, expected_resources, or any skill-specific term. The APE workflow (Zhou et al. 2022, generate-instruction-from-demonstrations, score-against-held-out-truth) provides the closest prior-art analog to hint-free dispatch.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-05\",\"label\":\"The end-to-end harness flow has 6 stages with one hard invariant: the expected-resource key NEVER crosses the dispatch boundary (stages 1-2 to 3). The scoring pipeline loads the key independently in stage 5, and contamination is a hard pre-dispatch gate in stage 2. Negative scenarios (irrelevance detection, adapted from BFCL v4) must be included in every batch.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-06\",\"label\":\"The expected-resource key uses set membership (not ordered list) for scoring — the AI can discover resources in any order. This accommodates the iteration-001 finding that skills do not have deterministic correct chains of resource loads; the same task can be solved by reading references in different orders.\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-07\",\"label\":\"Toolformer (Schick et al. 2023) self-supervised API-call annotation pipeline maps to Lane C trace capture — special tokens demarcate API calls at each generation step, and the filter-by-usefulness step (L+_i vs L-_i) maps to the D4 skill-on/skill-off comparison question: did the loaded resource actually help produce better output?\",\"iteration\":2}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-deepseek-i2-08\",\"label\":\"Trace depth vs breadth: two distinct metrics emerge — initialActivationLatency (tool-calls to first skill resource, measures time-to-activation) vs fullResourceCoverage (all skill resources eventually loaded, measures depth of exploration). Both are useful and should be reported separately rather than collapsed into one metric.\",\"iteration\":2}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/deltas/iter-002.jsonl","time":{"start":1780129107953,"end":1780129107958}},"id":"prt_e77f68c27001gR5FEaXRqECqpW","sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","messageID":"msg_e77f677d1001j5rFLjhe3YY60N"}}
